"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"out-of-bag","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"vYkhMsXxUX"}],"key":"Xf51gCNakw"},{"type":"text","value":" (OOB) samples can be used as a free internal validation set, without touching the held-out test set. We track the OOB accuracy as trees are added, illustrating that bagging error decreases and then plateaus — it does not go back up as ","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"lUXWPqItt9"},{"type":"inlineMath","value":"M","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"html":"<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span>","key":"Dqn8R9cu84"},{"type":"text","value":" grows, which is the practical signature of variance reduction.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"xJqEUXBmvs"}],"key":"D80QpnqPSP"}],"key":"doXP9PgudV"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","data":{"tags":[]},"children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"# Suppress warning due to inaccurate OOB estimation,\n# due to low amounts of trees\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\", category=UserWarning)","visibility":"hide","key":"bbd7SCktq6"},{"type":"outputs","id":"jjmtsaSqvojtaM1vafJr0","children":[],"visibility":"show","key":"CFeZpS3OV8"}],"visibility":"show","key":"jDAsm4jIfx"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"n_estimators_range = range(10, 301, 10)\noob_scores = []\n\nfor n in n_estimators_range:\n    rf_oob = sklearn.ensemble.RandomForestClassifier(\n        n_estimators=n, max_depth=None, oob_score=True, random_state=0,\n    )\n    rf_oob.fit(X_train, y_train)\n    oob_scores.append(rf_oob.oob_score_)\n\nplt.figure(figsize=(5, 4))\nplt.plot(list(n_estimators_range), oob_scores, \"o-\")\nplt.xlabel(\"Number of trees M\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Out-of-bag accuracy\")\nplt.title(\"Random forest: OOB accuracy vs. ensemble size\")\nplt.show()\n","key":"mOKKzH4rTj"},{"type":"outputs","id":"1YdG7qi0TUt_Sq1oG5lWJ","children":[{"type":"output","jupyter_data":{"output_type":"display_data","metadata":{},"data":{"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"779d975ed5daf0e6a17f941c36a47d49","path":"/build/779d975ed5daf0e6a17f941c36a47d49.png"},"text/plain":{"content":"<Figure size 500x400 with 1 Axes>","content_type":"text/plain"}}},"children":[],"key":"jeAEOHt5zM"}],"key":"gEBIc11k7C"}],"key":"G6k3aF0Apd"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Comparing a single tree to the random forest","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"WDzMobOH8m"}],"identifier":"comparing-a-single-tree-to-the-random-forest","label":"Comparing a single tree to the random forest","html_id":"comparing-a-single-tree-to-the-random-forest","implicit":true,"key":"GlPhCPJAxJ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To highlight the effect of bagging, we also fit a single decision tree of comparable depth and compare test accuracy.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"kJcPeuwxIh"}],"key":"wnNz57DrCw"}],"key":"Zp0js0fKef"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"tree = sklearn.tree.DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=3, random_state=0)\ntree.fit(X_train, y_train)\n\nmodels = {\n    \"Decision tree\": tree,\n    \"Random forest\": rf,\n}\naccuracies = {name: sklearn.metrics.accuracy_score(y_test, m.predict(X_test)) for name, m in models.items()}\n\nplt.figure(figsize=(5, 4))\nplt.bar(accuracies.keys(), accuracies.values(), color=[\"gray\", \"tab:blue\"])\nplt.ylabel(\"Test accuracy\")\nplt.ylim(0.8, 1.0)\nplt.title(\"Single tree vs. random forest\")\nplt.show()\n","key":"CC0vUNn1vc"},{"type":"outputs","id":"4wLz5QNRD0saDsGH7y0FF","children":[{"type":"output","jupyter_data":{"output_type":"display_data","metadata":{},"data":{"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"e8c02837288c43e025c541a8aef7496a","path":"/build/e8c02837288c43e025c541a8aef7496a.png"},"text/plain":{"content":"<Figure size 500x400 with 1 Axes>","content_type":"text/plain"}}},"children":[],"key":"ZEce1T7Sa5"}],"key":"Kirecwzdj4"}],"key":"gw5zCfvpiS"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Model evaluation","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"DuKreJBzqZ"}],"identifier":"model-evaluation","label":"Model evaluation","html_id":"model-evaluation","implicit":true,"key":"fsMEj99s1g"}],"key":"wIvMIgJIXF"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"cm = sklearn.metrics.confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_rf)\ndisp = sklearn.metrics.ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm, display_labels=cancer[\"target_names\"])\ndisp.plot(cmap=plt.cm.Blues)\nplt.title(\"Random forest confusion matrix\")\nplt.show()\n","key":"W7egAzv6UC"},{"type":"outputs","id":"8_11u6d4YdtBDu9czwzVN","children":[{"type":"output","jupyter_data":{"output_type":"display_data","metadata":{},"data":{"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"0d142e57ba055568ae17436fdadfc990","path":"/build/0d142e57ba055568ae17436fdadfc990.png"},"text/plain":{"content":"<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>","content_type":"text/plain"}}},"children":[],"key":"oGEefRixLR"}],"key":"uHeXyxgz6R"}],"key":"geRngDllKo"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Feature importance","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"luMYkAiBkm"}],"identifier":"feature-importance","label":"Feature importance","html_id":"feature-importance","implicit":true,"key":"DisQhClxEd"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As with a single tree, the forest provides an aggregated feature importance, averaged over all 200 trees.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"iUgsRHg12S"}],"key":"hKMnZvoeaR"}],"key":"zyK35SR1Vx"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"importances = rf.feature_importances_\norder = importances.argsort()[::-1][:8]\n\nplt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))\nplt.barh(\n    [cancer[\"feature_names\"][i] for i in order][::-1],\n    importances[order][::-1],\n)\nplt.xlabel(\"Importance\")\nplt.title(\"Random forest: top feature importances\")\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n","key":"zBakovN6Hi"},{"type":"outputs","id":"tQpSzMn3Zvh7dpc9OAgQW","children":[{"type":"output","jupyter_data":{"output_type":"display_data","metadata":{},"data":{"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"a71cc8b83886257f4999f76f17d83f57","path":"/build/a71cc8b83886257f4999f76f17d83f57.png"},"text/plain":{"content":"<Figure size 600x400 with 1 Axes>","content_type":"text/plain"}}},"children":[],"key":"jeg0Ra2sDS"}],"key":"xPR0AAdh4m"}],"key":"JfXAUF4Jfq"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Take-away","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"MWlpBlkbVM"}],"identifier":"take-away","label":"Take-away","html_id":"take-away","implicit":true,"key":"dXc9Sn8ssb"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Random forests are an excellent default choice for tabular data with limited resources: they require little preprocessing (no feature scaling), handle a mix of numerical and categorical features well, and are robust to hyperparameter choices — they rarely need extensive tuning, and adding more trees essentially never hurts. Their main weakness relative to boosting (companion notebook) is that they typically leave a bit of predictive performance on the table, since averaging independent trees reduces variance but does nothing to reduce bias.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"DS0dVcQiuD"}],"key":"OxaSUHfzpR"}],"key":"trrguf6kPy"}],"key":"q8uS6ayoXF"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Decision trees","url":"/docs/decision-trees","group":"Mathematical Modeling in Biotechnology"},"next":{"title":"Gradient boosting","url":"/docs/gradient-boost","group":"Mathematical Modeling in Biotechnology"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}